{"data":[{"type":"questionAttempts","id":"17586081","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/questionAttempts/17586081"},"attributes":{"position":0,"marks":1,"score":0,"answeredAt":"2025-09-30T08:25:13+09:30","options":[1],"response":null,"finalizedAt":"2025-09-30T08:25:13+09:30"},"relationships":{"user":{"data":{"type":"users","id":"50098"}},"questionSession":{"data":null},"session":{"data":null},"question":{"data":{"type":"questions","id":"15056"}},"bookmark":{"data":null}}}],"included":[{"type":"questions","id":"15056","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/questions/15056"},"attributes":{"optionProportions":[0.76,0,0,0.19,0.05]},"relationships":{"item":{"data":{"type":"items","id":"7744"}},"activeRevision":{"data":{"type":"questionRevisions","id":"67580"}}}},{"type":"items","id":"7744","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/items/7744"},"attributes":{"contentType":"question"},"relationships":{"content":{"data":{"type":"questions","id":"15056"}},"activeRevision":{"data":{"type":"itemRevisions","id":"53032"}},"tags":{"data":[{"type":"tags","id":"15"},{"type":"tags","id":"30"},{"type":"tags","id":"67"},{"type":"tags","id":"71"},{"type":"tags","id":"74"},{"type":"tags","id":"1170"},{"type":"tags","id":"1911"},{"type":"tags","id":"4933"},{"type":"tags","id":"4950"},{"type":"tags","id":"6488"},{"type":"tags","id":"8115"}]},"contributions":{"data":[{"type":"contributions","id":"18909"},{"type":"contributions","id":"18912"}]}},"meta":{"canRevise":false,"canManage":false,"canDelete":false}},{"type":"questionRevisions","id":"67580","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/questionRevisions/67580"},"attributes":{"stem":"\u003Cp\u003EA clinician needs to determine whether a patient\u0027s kidney disease is acute or chronic based on imaging findings.\u003C/p\u003E","stemQuestion":"Which one of the following best describes the relationship between kidney size on ultrasound and disease chronicity?","responseType":"sba","marks":1,"options":["Small scarred kidneys indicate chronic kidney disease","Normal-sized kidneys indicate chronic kidney disease","Small scarred kidneys indicate acute kidney injury","Enlarged kidneys indicate chronic kidney disease","Kidney size remains unchanged in both conditions"],"correctOptions":[0],"correctResponses":null,"explanation":"\u003Cp\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003ESmall scarred kidneys\u003C/strong\u003E are characteristic of chronic kidney disease, reflecting progressive atrophy and fibrosis over time. In contrast, acute kidney injury typically presents with normal or even enlarged kidneys due to inflammation and oedema.\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003EThe incorrect options can be explained:\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cul\u003E\u003Cli\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003ENormal-sized kidneys indicate chronic kidney disease\u003C/strong\u003E - Normal-sized kidneys are more typical of acute kidney injury\u003C/li\u003E\u003Cli\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003ESmall scarred kidneys indicate acute kidney injury\u003C/strong\u003E - Kidney shrinkage takes time and indicates chronicity\u003C/li\u003E\u003Cli\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003EEnlarged kidneys indicate chronic kidney disease\u003C/strong\u003E - While some chronic conditions can cause enlarged kidneys (like diabetic nephropathy), this is not a reliable indicator of chronicity\u003C/li\u003E\u003Cli\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003EKidney size remains unchanged in both conditions\u003C/strong\u003E - Kidney size changes significantly in chronic kidney disease\u003C/li\u003E\u003C/ul\u003E\u003Cp\u003EOther features that help distinguish chronic from acute kidney disease include:\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cul\u003E\u003Cli\u003EPrevious documented abnormal kidney function in chronic disease\u003C/li\u003E\u003Cli\u003EPresence of anaemia and renal osteodystrophy in chronic disease\u003C/li\u003E\u003Cli\u003ERate of onset of symptoms and biochemical changes\u003C/li\u003E\u003C/ul\u003E","optionExplanations":null,"learningPoints":["Small scarred kidneys on ultrasound indicate chronic kidney disease due to progressive atrophy and fibrosis","Acute kidney injury typically presents with normal or enlarged kidneys on imaging","Kidney size on ultrasound is one of the most reliable distinguishing features between acute and chronic kidney disease"],"references":["Chen TK, Knicely DH, Grams ME. Chronic Kidney Disease Diagnosis and Management: A Review. JAMA. 2019 Oct 1;322(13):1294-1304. doi: 10.1001/jama.2019.14745. PMID: 31573641; PMCID: PMC7015670.","Jennette, J. C., \u0026 D\u0027Agati, V. D. (2023). Heptinstall\u0027s Pathology of the Kidney. Lippincott Williams \u0026 Wilkins","Kumar, V., Abbas, A. K., \u0026 Aster, J. C. (Eds.). (2012). Robbins basic pathology e-book. Elsevier Health Science","Koeppen, B. M., \u0026 Stanton, B. A. (2018). Renal Physiology E-Book: Renal Physiology E-Book. Elsevier Health Sciences."]},"relationships":{"itemRevision":{"data":{"type":"itemRevisions","id":"53032"}},"question":{"data":{"type":"questions","id":"15056"}},"stemMedia":{"data":[]},"explanationMedia":{"data":[]}}},{"type":"itemRevisions","id":"53032","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/itemRevisions/53032"},"attributes":{"createdAt":"2024-12-05T19:28:55+10:30","updatedAt":"2024-12-05T19:30:41+10:30"},"relationships":{"item":{"data":{"type":"items","id":"7744"}},"content":{"data":{"type":"questionRevisions","id":"67580"}}},"meta":{"canDelete":false}},{"type":"tags","id":"15","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/tags/15"},"attributes":{"emoji":"\ud83e\udd54","name":"Nephrology","synonyms":["Renal"],"description":null,"position":null,"createdAt":null,"updatedAt":"2021-05-21T07:52:08+09:30"},"relationships":{"group":{"data":{"type":"tagGroups","id":"1"}},"heading":{"data":{"type":"tagHeadings","id":"1"}}},"meta":{"itemCount":0}},{"type":"tags","id":"30","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/tags/30"},"attributes":{"emoji":"\ud83c\udff4\u200d\u2620\ufe0f","name":"Radiology","synonyms":[],"description":null,"position":null,"createdAt":null,"updatedAt":"20